properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 20 at 4:52AM EST until January 21 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and waves
8 to 13 feet possible.

* WHERE...Lake Superior from Upper Entrance to Portage Canal to
Manitou Island MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian Border,
Eagle River to Manitou Island MI and Upper Entrance of Portage
Canal to Eagle River MI.

* WHEN...From late tonight through Tuesday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH TUESDAY AFTERNOON
